                <div type="textpart" n="D"><head>Plates: Tamil portion</head>
                    
                    <p n="85r8-86r14">
                        To those who do good to this <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> and to those who protect it the way I did/established it,
                        there should be the merit which is that of those who<note>That is, their merit should be equal to that of those who.</note>,
                        at the time of a solar eclipse,
                        in sacred places such as the confluence of the Ganges in the ocean, Vāraṇāsī, Sālagrāma, and Kurukṣetra,
                        make a donation of several thousands of tawny pregnant cows,
                        along with clothes, ornaments and land,
                        in favour of honourable experts in the four <foreign>veda</foreign>s, officiants for all sacrifices, who are poor, chiefs of large household, and knowing the <foreign>brahman</foreign>.
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>...</p>
                    
                    <p n="86v1-86v4">
                        To those who make destruction to this pious act and to those who ... with this destruction,
                        there should be the sin which is that of those who<note>That is, their sin should be equal to that of those who.</note>,
                        at the same time and same place,<note>That is, the sacred places just mentioned  in the above blessing.</note>
                        intentionally kill innocent ones like such cows, Brahmins and warriors.                        
                    </p>                    
                    
                    <p>...</p>
                    
                    <p n="86v8-86v9">This is the manner he graciously did after having graciously had this stipulation <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>samaiya</foreign> = <foreign>samaya</foreign></supplied> done having said so.</p>
                    
                    <p n="86v9-86v10">He says<note>The original reading is <foreign>collukiṉṟē<choice><orig>n</orig><reg>ṉ</reg></choice></foreign>, but one should probably understand <foreign>collukiṉṟār</foreign>.</note> <supplied reason="subaudible">so</supplied> looking<note>That is, having in mind.</note> at the kings who will come further.</p>
                    
                    <p n="86v10-86v13">He graciously gave this order to these assembly members, having graciously done it saying: <quote>Protect this pious act observing this stipulation and considering the benefit which lies in donating land, the sin which lies in seizing land, and the benefit which lies in protecting a pious donation.</quote></p>
                    
                    <p>...</p>
                                        
                </div>
                
